1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,880
 Jesus, in your name we pray, amen.

2
00:00:02,880 --> 00:00:04,360
 - Amen.

3
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:06,780
 Aw, so sweet.

4
00:00:06,780 --> 00:00:09,640
 Thanks, Justin.

5
00:00:09,640 --> 00:00:12,480
 Yeah, it's really, really good to be here.

6
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:15,960
 Definitely feels like I've, kind of a homecoming,

7
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:18,880
 coming back to my second family.

8
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:21,620
 I pretty much grew up in the vine,

9
00:00:21,620 --> 00:00:25,220
 and even before I knew Justin, I knew Andrew,

10
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:26,960
 back when he was much cooler then.

11
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:30,240
 He had long hair, ponytail, it's true,

12
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:35,240
 and he was a punk rock, death metal guy.

13
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,080
 You've come a long way, Andrew.

14
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:38,760
 Yeah, there is a God, there is a God.

15
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:41,160
 (laughing)

16
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:43,840
 Yeah, so it's really good, really good to be here.

17
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:46,360
 And speaking of family, this being a second home

18
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:47,920
 and a family, I wanna introduce you very quickly

19
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:50,700
 to the youngest member of my family.

20
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:53,160
 So, married with seven children,

21
00:00:53,160 --> 00:00:56,560
 and this is our youngest right here.

22
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:58,680
 Her name is Lily.

23
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:02,880
 Everyone say aw, yeah, so sweet.

24
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:06,320
 Now, of course, you don't have to be a professional parent

25
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:08,500
 to know that you're not allowed to have favorites, right?

26
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,480
 No favorites, okay?

27
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:14,040
 But I must say, she is the cutest one.

28
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:16,240
 All right, that's an objective thing, all right?

29
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,520
 It's a fact.

30
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:19,780
 She is the cutest, and she knows it, all right?

31
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:24,280
 Even her siblings, we all agree that she's the cutest, okay?

32
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:26,360
 But it's not just 'cause she's the little one,

33
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,680
 you know, she's cute.

34
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:30,520
 There's something else about her

35
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:33,600
 that I really, really appreciate and value,

36
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:36,760
 and that is just the fact that she's so vibrant

37
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:39,040
 and free and joyful.

38
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:42,680
 It seems like it just kind of emanates from her, right?

39
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:45,480
 And it's not something that is, you know,

40
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,880
 not something that is taught.

41
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,520
 It's something that she just carries

42
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,940
 from the day she was born.

43
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:52,760
 And I think all of our kids, when they were young,

44
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:56,160
 it seemed like that was something that they all walked in.

45
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,800
 This kind of freedom and joy

46
00:01:57,800 --> 00:02:00,440
 that I think is actually very infectious.

47
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,600
 It's something that I deeply envy,

48
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:05,080
 and something I think that we just need more of

49
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,880
 in this very serious city, Hong Kong, all right?

50
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,120
 Does anyone think sometimes we're a bit too serious here

51
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:10,960
 in the city?

52
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,160
 Yeah, a bit too serious.

53
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:15,440
 So it's that childlikeness is so beautiful.

54
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:17,680
 And sometimes I ask the Lord, you know,

55
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:20,920
 how come, why, where does this freedom

56
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,200
 and this joy come from?

57
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,060
 And again, I just wanna give a disclaimer.

58
00:02:25,060 --> 00:02:28,880
 I am not a professional child development expert.

59
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:31,060
 I don't have a PhD in this, okay?

60
00:02:31,060 --> 00:02:33,940
 But as I've studied scripture and science,

61
00:02:33,940 --> 00:02:37,140
 it's very clear that one of the main reasons

62
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:42,140
 is because Lily is just so well-loved.

63
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:45,680
 She's protected and she's championed,

64
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,280
 not just by her biological family,

65
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:49,040
 so me and my wife and the siblings,

66
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:51,800
 but by a whole village of people.

67
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,520
 So you can see here, this is literally

68
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:56,680
 a part of our village, part of our church,

69
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:57,960
 a group of them, a bunch of them,

70
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,780
 actually we live in the same building,

71
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:00,920
 in the same apartment building,

72
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:04,380
 doing life and church and family and mission together.

73
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:09,380
 And so it's pretty cool because I kinda feel like,

74
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:11,780
 the Lord reminded me of Matthew 3:17.

75
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:13,940
 When Jesus was baptized, you remember this?

76
00:03:13,940 --> 00:03:16,740
 The heavens opened and the light shined down on him.

77
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:18,160
 ♪ Oh ♪

78
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:20,360
 And then he heard the voice of God say,

79
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:24,860
 this is my son whom I love, with him I am well-pleased.

80
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:27,280
 And the Lord was just showing me that through the village,

81
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:30,180
 it's as if every day, she's hearing

82
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:32,620
 through a chorus of voices, young and old,

83
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:34,280
 different people, men and women,

84
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:37,400
 just reaffirming, reaffirming again and again

85
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:41,160
 her true identity, that she is a beloved daughter of God,

86
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:45,180
 and that with her, we are well-pleased.

87
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:48,200
 Now, through my work at Mother's Choice,

88
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,760
 I have met other kids in Hong Kong

89
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:53,880
 who have a very different experience.

90
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:56,640
 And so just very quickly, I wanna tell you two stories

91
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:59,800
 of something I've personally experienced,

92
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:04,800
 children who've had a very different growing up than Lily.

93
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:09,480
 And so the first one is a little boy, a little baby boy.

94
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,480
 When he first came to our home,

95
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:15,240
 so my wife and I, we volunteer as Safe Family Volunteers,

96
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,640
 where we help take care of little babies,

97
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:20,120
 provide baby care for single moms

98
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,080
 so that they can get some me time.

99
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:25,960
 And so when this baby first started coming to our home,

100
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:28,620
 he was only not even one years old yet.

101
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:30,820
 And when he first came in, the first thing we noticed

102
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:33,040
 was just how small he was.

103
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:35,560
 He was tiny for a one-year-old.

104
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:38,040
 And then we noticed that his clothes,

105
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,280
 they were stained and dirty,

106
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,040
 and he actually smelled like smoke.

107
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:46,940
 And we noticed that he had horrible eczema,

108
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:48,360
 and it hadn't been treated well.

109
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:52,040
 So many of his joints, they had been just scratched

110
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,160
 to the point of bleeding.

111
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,200
 And so he was actually bleeding in several places

112
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:58,240
 when he first showed up in our home.

113
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,960
 We also noticed that just the smallest noise,

114
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:03,400
 and you can imagine our home, seven kids,

115
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,240
 there's a lot of noise.

116
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,400
 It's a bit of a zoo.

117
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,960
 I see my full-time job, not with Mother's Choice

118
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:09,880
 or anything like that.

119
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:12,160
 I think I'm a zookeeper, really.

120
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,640
 It's a beautiful, it's a chaos,

121
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,640
 but it's a beautiful chaos.

122
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:17,080
 And so you can imagine this noise,

123
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:19,920
 and this baby would just, for the smallest noise,

124
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:23,880
 would just burst out crying and just out of control

125
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:27,380
 and just fearful, and it just didn't seem normal.

126
00:05:27,380 --> 00:05:29,140
 But what was most heartbreaking

127
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:32,740
 is that we noticed very quickly that this baby boy,

128
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:35,980
 he was gripping his thumb, his left thumb,

129
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:37,540
 very, very tightly.

130
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:39,180
 And when we tried to pull his thumb out,

131
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:40,300
 he couldn't use it.

132
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:41,620
 It was limp.

133
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:44,300
 And so we, of course, told the social worker,

134
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:46,480
 and then the social worker got it checked up

135
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:49,440
 with a therapist, and we found out that the problem,

136
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:53,720
 the reason it was like this is because this baby boy

137
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:58,720
 was stressed and had anxiety, was fearful.

138
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:02,680
 And I think when we look at Hong Kong,

139
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:05,520
 yes, we're aware of many young people in this city

140
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,920
 who struggle with depression, mental health issues,

141
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:10,880
 but I never once imagined that a one-year-old,

142
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:13,160
 not even a one-year-old baby,

143
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:15,680
 would already be struggling with anxiety

144
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:18,080
 and stress and fear.

145
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,780
 And so that was something that was very heartbreaking

146
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:20,740
 for my wife and I.

147
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:26,280
 Another couple, a friend, a couple that we know personally,

148
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:28,120
 they were a foster family through Mother's Choice,

149
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,840
 and they also shared about this other little boy

150
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,800
 who came to their home when he was only

151
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,120
 a year and a half old.

152
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:39,880
 And they quickly noticed that in between meals,

153
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:44,120
 he would be rummaging through the trash can, the garbage,

154
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:49,000
 looking for food, and they just wondered

155
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,460
 what could have happened to this boy

156
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:53,960
 that would cause him at not even two years old

157
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:56,120
 to be worried, fearful, thinking about

158
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,920
 where his next meal would come from.

159
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:00,360
 They also discovered that he would hide,

160
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:03,880
 put away bits of his meal, breakfast, lunch, or dinner,

161
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:08,240
 in different places in the home to hide it, to hoard it.

162
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:12,240
 Again, somehow this little boy,

163
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,160
 whatever he had experienced, whatever trauma he experienced

164
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:17,360
 had caused him to feel like he had to take care of himself,

165
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,560
 that no one would take care of him,

166
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:21,840
 and that he had to look out for his own well-being.

167
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:24,560
 Again, that is not the way it's supposed to be.

168
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,640
 That's not God's heart, that's not God's design.

169
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,480
 Something is wrong.

170
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:35,480
 Now, there are many, many more vulnerable, abused,

171
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,280
 and abandoned children in Hong Kong.

172
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:40,480
 There are a lot of stats,

173
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:42,080
 and I don't have time to go through all of them,

174
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,080
 but I want to highlight quickly.

175
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:47,400
 There are over 4,000 children in Hong Kong

176
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:50,760
 who have spent at least five years

177
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,120
 of their most formative years,

178
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:55,640
 oftentimes from zero, from birth, till five,

179
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:58,520
 they've spent at least five years in institutional care.

180
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:03,400
 That means outside of a safe, loving, and permanent family.

181
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:07,120
 And as I said, both science and scripture

182
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:11,160
 tell us that that does not set up a child for success.

183
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:13,440
 That does not set them up to thrive,

184
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:16,400
 at most, only to survive.

185
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:20,240
 There are another 600 to 700 kids right now,

186
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,720
 between the age of zero and one,

187
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:25,040
 who have never left their hospital crib.

188
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,640
 They were born, and they were just left in the hospital crib

189
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:31,000
 with no family or home to go to,

190
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:34,240
 nowhere safe for them to call home.

191
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:38,240
 Sometimes, these statistics, they're just numbers,

192
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:43,040
 and I try to put myself actually into one of these child's shoes

193
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:45,000
 to actually feel or think about

194
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,520
 what they are feeling and thinking.

195
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:53,120
 I'm sure that they are thinking and feeling

196
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:57,320
 and asking themselves, "Where is my mom?

197
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:59,920
 "Where is my dad?

198
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:02,120
 "How come no one wants me?

199
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:05,160
 "Why are there all these other children with families?

200
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,840
 "But I don't have a family.

201
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,880
 "Is it because I'm too ugly?

202
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:12,160
 "Is it because I'm not well-behaved enough?

203
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:15,200
 "Is it because I'm not smart enough, not pretty enough?

204
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:18,360
 "What did I do wrong?"

205
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:22,040
 And over time, they must begin to think some horrible lies,

206
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:24,960
 like, "I must be a mistake.

207
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,520
 "I don't deserve to be loved.

208
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:28,640
 "I'm just a piece of trash.

209
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,400
 "I don't deserve to be loved.

210
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,400
 "I'm just a piece of trash.

211
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,400
 "I don't deserve to live."

212
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:39,000
 These are all horrible lies and attacks of the enemy

213
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:44,000
 to steal, kill, and destroy families and our next generation.

214
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,720
 This is not something new.

215
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,720
 He's been doing this since the very beginning.

216
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,920
 Since the Garden of Eden,

217
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:52,080
 the enemy has been trying to tear down, break down,

218
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:55,160
 rip apart families and the next generation.

219
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:57,800
 Are we aware?

220
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:01,600
 How would you feel about this?

221
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,800
 Again, bring it a little closer to home.

222
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,520
 What if, and I know this is sensitive,

223
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:10,520
 but what if someone walked into your home this afternoon

224
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:14,520
 and attacked your kids or your siblings?

225
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:17,680
 How would you feel about that?

226
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:20,200
 Or what if someone just walked into the Sunday school here

227
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:23,640
 at the Vine Church and began to scream abuse

228
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:24,840
 at the Vine kids?

229
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,400
 How would you feel about that?

230
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:33,680
 Would you stand by and do nothing?

231
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:35,280
 Would you allow that to happen?

232
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:38,480
 Or would you take action?

233
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:44,520
 Now, even more importantly than what these children feel

234
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,720
 and what you and I may feel about this

235
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:51,280
 is how does our heavenly Father feel about this?

236
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:55,920
 We know from Psalms 139

237
00:10:58,680 --> 00:11:03,680
 that our heavenly Father, He sees and knows every child

238
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:06,400
 and that He, with His own two hands,

239
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,680
 lovingly formed every child

240
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:11,040
 while they were still in their mother's womb.

241
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,640
 He is their true Father.

242
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:17,360
 And because He made them and formed them,

243
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:19,720
 He gave them life, He also gave them a name.

244
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:22,120
 He knows their name.

245
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:26,160
 To us, they're just statistics and numbers and a case,

246
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:29,200
 but He sees every single one of them.

247
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:32,760
 Even as they are unborn, none of them are invisible to Him.

248
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:33,880
 He knows their name.

249
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,280
 He gave them a name.

250
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,640
 He gave them life.

251
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:38,880
 And He also has a future for them,

252
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:41,440
 a beautiful future for them, I believe.

253
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:47,680
 And that is why every time I think,

254
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:49,320
 how does the Father feel about this?

255
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:53,520
 I can't imagine just how broken His heart is.

256
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:57,520
 I can't imagine how much His heart is burning with anger

257
00:11:57,520 --> 00:12:01,880
 that anyone would dare to even touch or hurt or mistreat

258
00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:05,840
 one of His precious little ones, these innocent little ones.

259
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:10,400
 And this is why we see in Scripture some verses,

260
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:13,000
 I'll show you some verses that are pretty intense,

261
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,960
 but I just want you to know

262
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:18,480
 just how strongly our heavenly Father feels

263
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:19,760
 about this issue.

264
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:24,760
 So Exodus 22, verses 22 to 24,

265
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:27,960
 God is saying to Moses,

266
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:31,880
 "You must not exploit a widow or an orphan.

267
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:35,080
 "If you exploit them in any way and they cry out to Me,

268
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:38,240
 "then I will certainly hear their cry.

269
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,920
 "My anger will blaze against you

270
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,760
 "and I will kill you with a sword.

271
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,280
 "Then your wives will be widows

272
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:45,240
 "and your children fatherless."

273
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:48,640
 That's pretty intense.

274
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,920
 Yes, we can all acknowledge that, right?

275
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:52,800
 It's pretty intense, okay?

276
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:57,560
 In Isaiah 1, verses 15 to 17,

277
00:12:57,560 --> 00:13:00,840
 here through the prophet Isaiah,

278
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:04,960
 again, God is speaking to His people, okay?

279
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,800
 And He says to them,

280
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:10,240
 "When you lift up your hands in prayer, I will not look.

281
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:12,560
 "Though you offer many prayers, I will not listen,

282
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:13,680
 "for your hands are covered

283
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:15,920
 "with the blood of innocent victims.

284
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,740
 "Wash yourselves and be clean.

285
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:19,600
 "Get your sins out of My sight.

286
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:22,240
 "Give up your evil ways."

287
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,280
 Okay, and then He goes on to say,

288
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:25,680
 "This is how," in verse 17,

289
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:28,800
 "This is how you do that," all right?

290
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,680
 "This is how you get yourself in a place

291
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:33,240
 "where I do want to hear your prayers,

292
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:37,560
 "where I do want to hear and be with you

293
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:43,320
 "and all your cries, then that's when it matters to Me,

294
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:47,320
 "because I know that you are aligned with My heart

295
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,360
 "and not just doing what is good for you

296
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:53,360
 "and coming to a church gathering, for example,

297
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:55,240
 "just to get what you need,

298
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:58,000
 "but do you know what I care about?"

299
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,520
 This is what God is saying here.

300
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:01,320
 It's tough to hear.

301
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:02,320
 It's really tough to hear,

302
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:05,320
 and I'm challenged all the time by this.

303
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:07,080
 But the Lord says to them,

304
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:10,120
 "When you are ready to care about what I care about,

305
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,000
 "this is what I want you to do.

306
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,740
 "Learn to do good.

307
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:16,280
 "Seek justice.

308
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:18,220
 "Help the oppressed.

309
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:20,560
 "Defend the cause of orphans

310
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:23,600
 "and fight for the rights of widows."

311
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:28,200
 You see, church, before the Lord,

312
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,920
 it's not enough that we just ask Him,

313
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:34,320
 "How can we avoid evil?"

314
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,740
 Right, "How can we avoid evil?

315
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:37,520
 "How can we resist evil?"

316
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:42,400
 God is asking us to go further than that,

317
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,640
 to ask a different question,

318
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:48,580
 which is, "How can we do good?

319
00:14:48,580 --> 00:14:52,500
 "How can we do good?"

320
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:53,700
 There's a famous quote that says,

321
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:57,000
 "The only thing necessary for the triumph of evil

322
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,740
 "is for good men to do nothing."

323
00:14:59,740 --> 00:15:04,340
 Now, I know for some of you, you might be thinking,

324
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:08,620
 "Jason, this is very Old Testament-y,

325
00:15:08,620 --> 00:15:11,460
 "kind of wrath of God type of stuff you're saying.

326
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:14,400
 "You know, we're living now in the New Testament, right?

327
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,440
 "This is an age of grace.

328
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,060
 "You know, we were singing about songs just now

329
00:15:18,060 --> 00:15:20,060
 "that made us feel really warm inside,

330
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:22,560
 "and, you know, I don't know if this is really,

331
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:25,120
 "you know, speaking to me."

332
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:29,920
 And so, just to make sure that we're all clear,

333
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:33,620
 this is the same God in the Old and in the New Testament.

334
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:36,220
 And in fact, in the New Testament,

335
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:39,500
 God is even more clear and direct.

336
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:42,340
 Okay, He says, through the Apostle James,

337
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:47,060
 "Pure and genuine religion in the sight of God the Father

338
00:15:47,060 --> 00:15:50,400
 "means caring for orphans and widows in their distress

339
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:53,200
 "and refusing to let the world corrupt you."

340
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:58,900
 Don't you love it when God gives us a formula?

341
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:01,700
 All right, it's black and white.

342
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:02,840
 It's really clear.

343
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:04,500
 It's really easy.

344
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:07,840
 Unfortunately, we know that the most simple,

345
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,920
 direct things sometimes in Scripture

346
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:12,160
 are the hardest things to do.

347
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:15,340
 All right, so I'm not pointing a finger at anyone.

348
00:16:15,340 --> 00:16:16,340
 All right, this is something, again,

349
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:18,840
 that I am constantly challenging myself,

350
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:21,860
 our community, our family.

351
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:24,480
 Do we feel what He feels?

352
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:28,280
 Do we care about what He cares about?

353
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:33,860
 Is our faith, our Christianity, our walk with God,

354
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:39,480
 is it pure and genuine in His eyes?

355
00:16:42,060 --> 00:16:45,420
 Now, thank heavens that our God,

356
00:16:45,420 --> 00:16:49,420
 He is in the business of making all things right

357
00:16:49,420 --> 00:16:50,460
 and all things new.

358
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:54,100
 He is the God of redemption.

359
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:55,740
 So what that mean, amen?

360
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:58,360
 Amen, so that means that He is not just there

361
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:02,180
 wringing His hands in stress and heartbroken and teary-eyed.

362
00:17:02,180 --> 00:17:05,340
 Oh, He's angry but powerless.

363
00:17:05,340 --> 00:17:10,340
 No, our God, He has a plan,

364
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:14,140
 a glorious plan for redemption

365
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:18,180
 to redeem and restore and transform the orphan,

366
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:20,520
 the widow, the refugee, the vulnerable.

367
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:23,020
 And that is exciting.

368
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:24,980
 But do we know what His plan is?

369
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:30,500
 Is His plan to, you know, we need more,

370
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:32,700
 to have more institutional care

371
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:34,800
 or to train up more social workers?

372
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:39,120
 Or is it to start up more NGOs like Mother's Choice?

373
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:41,820
 Now, don't get me wrong.

374
00:17:41,820 --> 00:17:43,340
 You know, I get, you know,

375
00:17:43,340 --> 00:17:44,580
 Mother's Choice pays my bills, right?

376
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:49,580
 So it's obviously clear that all of these things,

377
00:17:49,580 --> 00:17:51,340
 these parties I mentioned,

378
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:55,340
 they all are important and have a valuable role to play

379
00:17:55,340 --> 00:17:57,620
 in the care of orphans and widows.

380
00:17:57,620 --> 00:17:59,380
 But it's not God's design.

381
00:17:59,380 --> 00:18:02,660
 God's design is very clear that the primary instrument

382
00:18:02,660 --> 00:18:05,980
 for redemption and transformation are not those things.

383
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:08,480
 It's something else.

384
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:12,540
 And so I just wanna very quickly go through a story

385
00:18:12,540 --> 00:18:17,300
 in scripture that tells us what God's plan is,

386
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:22,300
 His primary instrument for redemption for the fatherless.

387
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:24,820
 Now, I don't have time to go through the whole story today.

388
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:26,780
 You can go read it on your own.

389
00:18:26,780 --> 00:18:27,620
 It's very readable.

390
00:18:27,620 --> 00:18:30,460
 It's very short, 2 Samuel 9.

391
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:34,700
 And basically what happens is King David,

392
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:35,900
 he has established his throne.

393
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:37,640
 He has defeated all his enemies.

394
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:40,160
 And so as he's comfortably sitting there,

395
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,700
 he's thinking, what about, what happened to Jonathan?

396
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:44,100
 What happened to his family, right?

397
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:47,360
 His best friend, Jonathan, which was Saul's son, right?

398
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:48,600
 His arch enemy, Saul, right?

399
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:52,700
 Who he defeated, okay, to take over the kingdom, right?

400
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:56,780
 And he finds out that there is a crippled orphan

401
00:18:56,780 --> 00:19:01,100
 named Mephibosheth, who is the grandson of King Saul.

402
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:04,060
 So his enemy's grandson.

403
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:07,340
 And out of God's kindness, it says in the scripture,

404
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:10,100
 out of God's kindness, he welcomes him.

405
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:12,420
 He calls him to come to the palace.

406
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:15,360
 And you can imagine Mephibosheth is very scared,

407
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:17,600
 shaking in his boots because he doesn't know

408
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:18,440
 why he's being called.

409
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:20,020
 Is it because they wanna kill him

410
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:23,060
 so that bloodline is finished, right?

411
00:19:23,060 --> 00:19:26,660
 Very Game of Thrones, K-drama-ish type stuff going on here.

412
00:19:26,660 --> 00:19:28,260
 All right?

413
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:31,860
 So he comes in and he's scared.

414
00:19:31,860 --> 00:19:35,940
 And he says, why have you called me, oh, great one, David?

415
00:19:35,940 --> 00:19:38,020
 I am just a dead dog.

416
00:19:38,020 --> 00:19:41,260
 And then David says to him,

417
00:19:41,260 --> 00:19:46,180
 so now I'm jumping to verse nine, okay?

418
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:51,180
 The king then summons a servant named Ziba, okay?

419
00:19:51,180 --> 00:19:55,120
 And says, I have given your master's grandson,

420
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:58,060
 that's Mephibosheth, everything that belonged to Saul

421
00:19:58,060 --> 00:19:58,900
 and his family.

422
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,460
 Wow, that's a lot, okay?

423
00:20:00,460 --> 00:20:01,860
 A king's inheritance.

424
00:20:01,860 --> 00:20:04,660
 He's giving that back to Mephibosheth.

425
00:20:04,660 --> 00:20:06,700
 You and your sons and servants, Ziba,

426
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:08,700
 are now to farm the land for him

427
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:10,820
 and produce food for your master's household.

428
00:20:10,820 --> 00:20:13,780
 All right, so providing sustenance, right?

429
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:16,580
 Food, sustenance, provision,

430
00:20:16,580 --> 00:20:19,980
 giving him a place to stay, amazing, okay?

431
00:20:19,980 --> 00:20:21,500
 But on top of that, right?

432
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,980
 It goes further down.

433
00:20:22,980 --> 00:20:24,740
 And so Ziba says, yes, Lord, I'll do all that.

434
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:26,140
 And then the last line there.

435
00:20:26,140 --> 00:20:30,020
 And from that time on, Mephibosheth ate regularly

436
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:35,020
 at David's table like one of the king's own sons.

437
00:20:35,020 --> 00:20:39,260
 This is the part I wanna make sure we get.

438
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:44,260
 Yes, David gave him a place to live, gave him food to eat.

439
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:47,360
 And that came at a high cost to him

440
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:50,900
 'cause he gave a king's inheritance back to Mephibosheth.

441
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:53,500
 But that wasn't what was most significant.

442
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:54,940
 What was most significant

443
00:20:54,940 --> 00:20:57,380
 is that David then welcomed him.

444
00:20:57,380 --> 00:20:59,780
 Mephibosheth, this crippled orphan

445
00:20:59,780 --> 00:21:05,260
 that was his enemy's grandson into his own family,

446
00:21:05,260 --> 00:21:09,740
 to his own table and treated him like his very own son.

447
00:21:09,740 --> 00:21:13,820
 Wow, you can imagine the risk

448
00:21:13,820 --> 00:21:18,180
 that he was taking in doing this, right?

449
00:21:18,180 --> 00:21:21,220
 It's just crazy that he would do something like this.

450
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:24,260
 But we see that by rooting Mephibosheth

451
00:21:24,260 --> 00:21:27,860
 in this safe, loving family, in his own home.

452
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:29,780
 A few years later in 2 Samuel 19,

453
00:21:29,780 --> 00:21:31,580
 again, I don't have time to go into it now,

454
00:21:31,580 --> 00:21:33,780
 but please do some homework, look it up.

455
00:21:33,780 --> 00:21:36,300
 It's the epilogue, all right, of Mephibosheth.

456
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:37,500
 It's amazing.

457
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:40,340
 Years later, when Ziba, this Ziba guy,

458
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,820
 he'd actually turned out to be a bad guy,

459
00:21:41,820 --> 00:21:46,740
 he tried to scam and cheat Mephibosheth out of all his wealth.

460
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:48,940
 I'm just summarizing here.

461
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:50,620
 But Mephibosheth basically says,

462
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:51,460
 "You know what?

463
00:21:51,460 --> 00:21:52,520
 "Those things don't matter to me.

464
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:55,020
 "I don't need money or wealth or the kingdom.

465
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:58,320
 "All that matters is my relationship with you,

466
00:21:58,320 --> 00:21:59,880
 "my father, David."

467
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:02,460
 Amazing.

468
00:22:02,460 --> 00:22:07,460
 Through this loving family, this home that David provided,

469
00:22:07,460 --> 00:22:11,820
 Mephibosheth was redeemed from being a dead dog.

470
00:22:11,820 --> 00:22:15,060
 He called himself a dead dog, less than human.

471
00:22:15,060 --> 00:22:19,800
 From being a dead dog, he was redeemed into a true son.

472
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:23,460
 His royal identity was restored.

473
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:28,460
 And so we see that God's plan is to restore broken family

474
00:22:28,460 --> 00:22:32,100
 through his family, not just biological family,

475
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:34,620
 but through the family of God.

476
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:39,020
 And this is who he is.

477
00:22:39,020 --> 00:22:41,020
 It's not just what he does, it is who he is,

478
00:22:41,020 --> 00:22:43,580
 because he is the father to the fatherless.

479
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:45,180
 He is the defender of widows.

480
00:22:45,180 --> 00:22:47,580
 He puts the lonely in families.

481
00:22:47,580 --> 00:22:50,080
 This is who our God is.

482
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:53,100
 And something I wanna highlight that I think is so cool

483
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:56,340
 is that who wrote this passage?

484
00:22:56,340 --> 00:22:58,580
 Who wrote this Psalm?

485
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:01,780
 It was David.

486
00:23:01,780 --> 00:23:03,460
 It was actually David who wrote this Psalm.

487
00:23:03,460 --> 00:23:05,540
 And we know the scriptures tell us in Acts 13

488
00:23:05,540 --> 00:23:09,440
 that David was a man after God's own heart.

489
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:13,540
 And what were some of the things that made him a man

490
00:23:13,540 --> 00:23:14,460
 after God's own heart?

491
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:17,860
 Well, he often did things that were crazy

492
00:23:17,860 --> 00:23:19,380
 or shameful even, right?

493
00:23:19,380 --> 00:23:22,300
 He danced in his underwear in front of the whole nation.

494
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:25,220
 All right, he spared his enemy Saul

495
00:23:25,220 --> 00:23:26,740
 when he should have killed him.

496
00:23:26,740 --> 00:23:27,720
 Everyone thought he should have killed him.

497
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,260
 God's given you your enemy.

498
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:30,980
 Take it, take the kingdom.

499
00:23:30,980 --> 00:23:33,440
 No, he did things that were shameful and foolish

500
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:38,440
 in the eyes of man, but were pleasing in God's eyes.

501
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:41,100
 And I believe that when he took in Mephibosheth,

502
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:44,380
 his enemy's grandson, this orphan, this crippled orphan,

503
00:23:44,380 --> 00:23:47,900
 that was less than a dead dog,

504
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:49,300
 and brought him into his own home

505
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,980
 and treated him like his very own son,

506
00:23:50,980 --> 00:23:53,820
 it was one of those things that God ticked and said,

507
00:23:53,820 --> 00:23:56,680
 "This is a man after my own heart."

508
00:23:56,680 --> 00:24:02,580
 And so, I don't know about you, like David,

509
00:24:02,580 --> 00:24:06,180
 I hope that I can be someone who can also make room

510
00:24:06,180 --> 00:24:09,080
 at my table for the fatherless,

511
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:12,620
 and at your tables, at our tables,

512
00:24:12,620 --> 00:24:14,820
 not primarily for their sake,

513
00:24:14,820 --> 00:24:18,420
 but first and foremost, for his sake,

514
00:24:18,420 --> 00:24:23,820
 that we may all strive to become men and women

515
00:24:23,820 --> 00:24:26,340
 after God's own heart.

516
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:29,740
 Guys, this is not about doing social work.

517
00:24:29,740 --> 00:24:31,940
 This is not about just responding to,

518
00:24:31,940 --> 00:24:35,580
 "Oh, kids, poor kids, oh, sad story."

519
00:24:35,580 --> 00:24:38,440
 It's first and foremost about responding to his heart

520
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:40,780
 because we love him and we wanna become more like him.

521
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:42,660
 We wanna know his heartbeat.

522
00:24:42,660 --> 00:24:44,340
 We wanna feel what he feels,

523
00:24:44,340 --> 00:24:47,880
 and we wanna comfort his heart and bring joy to his heart.

524
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:49,740
 That's who we are forever.

525
00:24:49,740 --> 00:24:50,920
 We are missionaries.

526
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:53,220
 Oh, sorry, we are worshipers forever.

527
00:24:53,220 --> 00:24:54,500
 We are worshipers forever,

528
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:57,600
 and this is our worship unto him.

529
00:24:57,600 --> 00:25:01,560
 So the story of Mephibosheth,

530
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:04,300
 I've said it so many times, I've gotten a bit,

531
00:25:04,300 --> 00:25:07,860
 M, Mephibosheth, M, all right?

532
00:25:07,860 --> 00:25:12,020
 The story of M, it's great, but it can be easy.

533
00:25:12,020 --> 00:25:13,280
 I'm just giving myself a break here.

534
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:17,260
 It can be easy to treat it as a little bit of a fairy tale,

535
00:25:17,260 --> 00:25:20,180
 right, you know, Old Testament children's stories, right?

536
00:25:20,180 --> 00:25:21,080
 It's a bit of a fairy tale,

537
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:23,860
 just like David killing Goliath, you know?

538
00:25:23,860 --> 00:25:26,500
 Doesn't seem so relevant to us here in Hong Kong today,

539
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:29,980
 right, it can feel like so far, far away.

540
00:25:29,980 --> 00:25:32,600
 It just doesn't seem like something that applies

541
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:34,860
 to our lifestyles here in Hong Kong,

542
00:25:34,860 --> 00:25:36,820
 and so I wanted to share one more story

543
00:25:36,820 --> 00:25:39,420
 that I hope will be closer to home,

544
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:41,500
 and you know, it's a Hong Kong story,

545
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:44,820
 and so hopefully you will find it more relevant.

546
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:49,820
 And so this story starts in the late 1940s, I think 1949,

547
00:25:49,820 --> 00:25:54,840
 and you see here this boy, he was born to his mother there,

548
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:56,120
 but there's no father in the picture

549
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:57,780
 because the father left.

550
00:25:57,780 --> 00:26:00,260
 His father left when he was born,

551
00:26:00,260 --> 00:26:03,360
 and he never met his father until he was 18,

552
00:26:04,180 --> 00:26:07,980
 and so you can imagine what it was like for his mother.

553
00:26:07,980 --> 00:26:11,460
 His mother was angry, heartbroken.

554
00:26:11,460 --> 00:26:15,700
 She did not want to even see this child,

555
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:20,380
 just being with this child reminded her of her own rejection,

556
00:26:20,380 --> 00:26:21,640
 how she was abandoned,

557
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:24,820
 in a sense her own shame and her own failure,

558
00:26:24,820 --> 00:26:28,880
 and so shortly at around the age of four or five years old,

559
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:31,020
 she decided she just couldn't handle it anymore,

560
00:26:31,020 --> 00:26:33,420
 and so she sent off this boy, her son,

561
00:26:33,420 --> 00:26:36,580
 to boarding school in Hong Kong at the age of five.

562
00:26:36,580 --> 00:26:41,260
 You can imagine, boarding school is a tough place

563
00:26:41,260 --> 00:26:46,060
 already on its own, but even more so

564
00:26:46,060 --> 00:26:47,940
 if you don't have a family,

565
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:49,220
 you don't have a father and mother,

566
00:26:49,220 --> 00:26:51,520
 people to protect you, care for you,

567
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:53,140
 look out for you, encourage you,

568
00:26:53,140 --> 00:26:58,140
 and so this young boy, he quickly became a very angry boy.

569
00:26:58,140 --> 00:27:00,820
 He got into fights all the times,

570
00:27:00,820 --> 00:27:03,460
 he got into arguments, not just with fights and arguments

571
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:07,100
 with other students, but with the teachers as well,

572
00:27:07,100 --> 00:27:08,700
 and he got into so much trouble,

573
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:11,940
 and that he actually got kicked out of school,

574
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:14,940
 not just once, but twice,

575
00:27:14,940 --> 00:27:17,500
 and then each time the school would let him back in

576
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:19,060
 because they felt sorry for him,

577
00:27:19,060 --> 00:27:20,980
 no, poor kid, so they let him back in,

578
00:27:20,980 --> 00:27:23,660
 but just there was too much, I think, anger,

579
00:27:23,660 --> 00:27:29,380
 trauma, bitterness in this boy's heart,

580
00:27:29,380 --> 00:27:31,420
 and so he couldn't help himself.

581
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:33,780
 Again, he got into more trouble,

582
00:27:33,780 --> 00:27:35,180
 and so finally they kicked him out of school

583
00:27:35,180 --> 00:27:39,100
 for the third time, they just couldn't deal with him anymore

584
00:27:39,100 --> 00:27:41,460
 and so he had nowhere to go, his mom didn't want him,

585
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:44,780
 so he actually got a room, a dorm room,

586
00:27:44,780 --> 00:27:47,980
 at the YMCA in TST next to the peninsula,

587
00:27:47,980 --> 00:27:52,220
 so clarify, not the peninsula, but next to the peninsula,

588
00:27:52,220 --> 00:27:54,740
 okay, a little dorm room there,

589
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:58,200
 and while he was there, he met a couple,

590
00:27:59,060 --> 00:28:02,460
 a New Zealand missionary couple

591
00:28:02,460 --> 00:28:04,660
 that were actually working at the YMCA at the time

592
00:28:04,660 --> 00:28:06,460
 as the general secretary,

593
00:28:06,460 --> 00:28:09,820
 and so they actually lived in the YMCA as well,

594
00:28:09,820 --> 00:28:11,620
 and so they got to know this little boy,

595
00:28:11,620 --> 00:28:13,700
 by this time he was a preteen, around 12, 13,

596
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:16,620
 they got to know him, they got to hear his story,

597
00:28:16,620 --> 00:28:18,660
 and they began to see into his soul,

598
00:28:18,660 --> 00:28:21,740
 and they began to realize just how much darkness was there,

599
00:28:21,740 --> 00:28:24,900
 how much anger and trauma and rage

600
00:28:24,900 --> 00:28:26,980
 and bitterness and sadness.

601
00:28:26,980 --> 00:28:29,420
 Clearly he had asked all those questions,

602
00:28:29,420 --> 00:28:32,820
 where's my dad, where's my mom, why don't they want me?

603
00:28:32,820 --> 00:28:34,540
 What's wrong with me?

604
00:28:34,540 --> 00:28:36,380
 They saw all that in him,

605
00:28:36,380 --> 00:28:39,820
 and they saw that he was on a very dark and dangerous road,

606
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:41,660
 they had no idea where he would end up,

607
00:28:41,660 --> 00:28:44,220
 they were worried about him, his future,

608
00:28:44,220 --> 00:28:46,460
 and so they decided to take him in,

609
00:28:46,460 --> 00:28:50,460
 and to give him a home, to make room at their table

610
00:28:50,460 --> 00:28:53,540
 for this young man.

611
00:28:55,620 --> 00:28:57,380
 They started to teach him English,

612
00:28:57,380 --> 00:29:01,820
 they started to bring him to Sunday school,

613
00:29:01,820 --> 00:29:04,300
 at Calhoun Union Church, every Sunday,

614
00:29:04,300 --> 00:29:05,820
 brought him to Sunday school,

615
00:29:05,820 --> 00:29:07,420
 he would hear the Sunday school stories,

616
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:08,740
 a lot of seeds were sown,

617
00:29:08,740 --> 00:29:12,580
 but they did something else that was very genius,

618
00:29:12,580 --> 00:29:16,820
 they gave him a job at the YMCA, in the hotel,

619
00:29:16,820 --> 00:29:19,940
 as a bellboy, so he would be moving luggage

620
00:29:19,940 --> 00:29:22,300
 and pushing moving boxes around and things all day,

621
00:29:22,300 --> 00:29:23,180
 so at the end of the day,

622
00:29:23,180 --> 00:29:25,340
 he had no energy left to get into fights.

623
00:29:25,340 --> 00:29:29,620
 Parenting, this is one of those parenting hacks,

624
00:29:29,620 --> 00:29:31,460
 now, you may have to adapt it a bit,

625
00:29:31,460 --> 00:29:33,340
 because I don't think it really,

626
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:34,460
 with child protection these days,

627
00:29:34,460 --> 00:29:38,900
 it might not be legal to do that with your kid,

628
00:29:38,900 --> 00:29:40,700
 but the point was that it worked,

629
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:44,540
 and obviously the most important thing is that

630
00:29:44,540 --> 00:29:48,060
 they made room for him, in their heart, in their home,

631
00:29:48,060 --> 00:29:50,620
 and they treated him like their very own son,

632
00:29:50,620 --> 00:29:53,140
 and so very shortly after that,

633
00:29:53,140 --> 00:29:55,260
 things started to change for him,

634
00:29:55,260 --> 00:29:57,180
 he got into LaSalle College,

635
00:29:57,180 --> 00:29:58,300
 you guys have heard of LaSalle?

636
00:29:58,300 --> 00:30:01,260
 It's one of the top boys schools, I said one of,

637
00:30:01,260 --> 00:30:03,380
 'cause I don't know, there might be some DBS boys here,

638
00:30:03,380 --> 00:30:06,980
 and I don't want you to leave the room in a huff,

639
00:30:06,980 --> 00:30:08,660
 don't be offended, I said one of,

640
00:30:08,660 --> 00:30:12,660
 so this boy, he got into LaSalle,

641
00:30:12,660 --> 00:30:14,260
 and not just that, when he graduated,

642
00:30:14,260 --> 00:30:16,700
 he was head boy, prefect,

643
00:30:16,700 --> 00:30:20,420
 after that, he got into Hong Kong U Law School,

644
00:30:20,420 --> 00:30:22,940
 and graduated the first law class,

645
00:30:22,940 --> 00:30:25,380
 law school class of Hong Kong U,

646
00:30:25,380 --> 00:30:27,220
 and all his peers who graduated with him

647
00:30:27,220 --> 00:30:29,700
 went on to be chief justices,

648
00:30:29,700 --> 00:30:32,180
 and start their own law firms in Hong Kong,

649
00:30:32,180 --> 00:30:34,020
 he graduated with honors,

650
00:30:34,020 --> 00:30:36,820
 and then he got into Stanford Law School,

651
00:30:36,820 --> 00:30:39,420
 and graduated with honors from there as well,

652
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:41,900
 and then began an illustrious career

653
00:30:41,900 --> 00:30:44,820
 as a corporate lawyer in Hong Kong,

654
00:30:44,820 --> 00:30:48,300
 and he went on to become one of the youngest partners

655
00:30:48,300 --> 00:30:51,460
 in one of the most esteemed law firms,

656
00:30:51,460 --> 00:30:53,580
 more than that, more importantly,

657
00:30:53,580 --> 00:30:55,060
 he became a Christian,

658
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:58,740
 and he decided that he wanted to use his legal expertise,

659
00:30:58,740 --> 00:31:01,260
 his gifts, his training,

660
00:31:01,260 --> 00:31:03,780
 to begin to serve and to build the kingdom,

661
00:31:03,780 --> 00:31:06,500
 and so he came alongside as an advisor,

662
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:08,380
 a legal advisor on the board,

663
00:31:08,380 --> 00:31:09,220
 and many other things,

664
00:31:09,220 --> 00:31:11,380
 a consultant for so many different churches,

665
00:31:11,380 --> 00:31:14,900
 and NGOs, and ministries, and missions agencies,

666
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:17,060
 he did so much work for the kingdom,

667
00:31:17,940 --> 00:31:21,100
 more importantly, he became,

668
00:31:21,100 --> 00:31:24,420
 most importantly, he became a man,

669
00:31:24,420 --> 00:31:27,500
 probably one of the most kind,

670
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:29,980
 and generous, and sacrificial,

671
00:31:29,980 --> 00:31:33,500
 and upright men in his generation,

672
00:31:33,500 --> 00:31:36,940
 truly servant-hearted unto the Lord,

673
00:31:36,940 --> 00:31:40,420
 and the reason I know that he's a good man

674
00:31:40,420 --> 00:31:43,300
 is because he's my dad.

675
00:31:44,300 --> 00:31:47,460
 (audience applauding)

676
00:31:47,460 --> 00:31:55,500
 The guy in the back, in case you wanted to,

677
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:57,700
 it's him.

678
00:31:57,700 --> 00:32:01,860
 Now, there's so much more to this story,

679
00:32:01,860 --> 00:32:04,060
 but I just want to highlight a few more things.

680
00:32:04,060 --> 00:32:08,500
 When I was, I think, early teen,

681
00:32:08,500 --> 00:32:13,260
 my dad reconnected with his dad.

682
00:32:14,260 --> 00:32:17,100
 Forgave him, reconciled with him,

683
00:32:17,100 --> 00:32:20,580
 and together with my mom, led his dad to the Lord,

684
00:32:20,580 --> 00:32:24,820
 and baptized his dad before he passed away.

685
00:32:24,820 --> 00:32:27,900
 Isn't that awesome?

686
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:31,060
 (audience applauding)

687
00:32:31,060 --> 00:32:36,300
 My dad also played an instrumental role

688
00:32:36,300 --> 00:32:37,900
 in helping start Mother's Choice.

689
00:32:37,900 --> 00:32:42,180
 He was the lawyer who helped with the paperwork,

690
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:45,100
 Section 88, NGO status, all that.

691
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:52,500
 It's beautiful how God can turn things

692
00:32:52,500 --> 00:32:56,460
 that were broken into, bring them full circle

693
00:32:56,460 --> 00:33:00,460
 into a blessing, not just for him, but for many others,

694
00:33:00,460 --> 00:33:04,340
 and personally, what I'm most blessed by

695
00:33:04,340 --> 00:33:08,500
 is that I think my dad, he passed on to me

696
00:33:08,500 --> 00:33:11,140
 and my family and our community.

697
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:14,380
 A special grace, a spiritual inheritance,

698
00:33:14,380 --> 00:33:19,380
 a spiritual legacy, that grace to adopt and to foster.

699
00:33:19,380 --> 00:33:23,820
 And so you can see in this picture, you can guess,

700
00:33:23,820 --> 00:33:27,340
 my wife and I, our family, we've been fostering

701
00:33:27,340 --> 00:33:30,660
 two teenage boys, they're brothers, they're orphans,

702
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:34,340
 as well as asylum seekers, and they've been in our family

703
00:33:34,340 --> 00:33:36,300
 for the last year and a half, Fabrice and Samuel,

704
00:33:36,300 --> 00:33:39,220
 and I've asked them for permission to show this photo.

705
00:33:39,220 --> 00:33:44,220
 And I tell you, that has been such a crazy adventure.

706
00:33:44,220 --> 00:33:49,900
 It's been one of the hardest things we've ever done

707
00:33:49,900 --> 00:33:53,780
 as a family, as a community, but also one of the most

708
00:33:53,780 --> 00:33:56,860
 formative and fulfilling things

709
00:33:56,860 --> 00:33:58,820
 that we've ever been a part of.

710
00:33:58,820 --> 00:34:02,660
 And that's why my family and our community,

711
00:34:02,660 --> 00:34:06,180
 we give thanks all the time that God brought

712
00:34:06,180 --> 00:34:08,580
 Fabrice and Samuel to us.

713
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:11,340
 And every chance I get, I tell Fabrice and Samuel,

714
00:34:11,340 --> 00:34:13,420
 in the face, in the eyes, I tell them,

715
00:34:13,420 --> 00:34:15,460
 thank you for trusting us.

716
00:34:15,460 --> 00:34:17,980
 Thank you for being a part of our family.

717
00:34:17,980 --> 00:34:21,220
 You, too, are a gift from God.

718
00:34:21,220 --> 00:34:23,700
 You're not a burden, you are a blessing.

719
00:34:23,700 --> 00:34:26,060
 Thank you, thank you.

720
00:34:26,060 --> 00:34:29,740
 And it's just icing on the cake that my wife and I

721
00:34:29,740 --> 00:34:33,620
 got to baptize Fabrice a couple months ago.

722
00:34:33,620 --> 00:34:36,220
 (audience applauding)

723
00:34:36,220 --> 00:34:38,020
 You see Samuel kind of lurking there?

724
00:34:38,860 --> 00:34:40,500
 Being little brother, all right?

725
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:43,740
 Just kind of lurking there, but it's been beautiful.

726
00:34:43,740 --> 00:34:46,300
 And this is not why we do this.

727
00:34:46,300 --> 00:34:49,300
 But again, like I said, it's not for this, right?

728
00:34:49,300 --> 00:34:53,420
 Again, it's not about the fruit that comes out of it.

729
00:34:53,420 --> 00:34:56,460
 It's about our faithfulness to what God has called us to do.

730
00:34:56,460 --> 00:35:03,380
 And so, as you can see here, just in real time,

731
00:35:03,380 --> 00:35:05,820
 hopefully the Word becoming flesh,

732
00:35:05,820 --> 00:35:08,980
 you can see that through the care and safety and stability

733
00:35:08,980 --> 00:35:11,860
 of a loving family and community,

734
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:15,740
 God truly can redeem broken stories

735
00:35:15,740 --> 00:35:17,660
 and turn them into beautiful testimonies,

736
00:35:17,660 --> 00:35:21,420
 not just for my father, but for many.

737
00:35:21,420 --> 00:35:26,180
 I believe for all of the children that are fatherless,

738
00:35:26,180 --> 00:35:27,940
 that are vulnerable in this city,

739
00:35:27,940 --> 00:35:30,460
 God has that upon His heart.

740
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:32,740
 That's what He wants to see happen.

741
00:35:32,740 --> 00:35:36,220
 But He's inviting you and I to take part

742
00:35:36,220 --> 00:35:37,780
 in this story of redemption,

743
00:35:37,780 --> 00:35:39,100
 this beautiful story of redemption.

744
00:35:39,100 --> 00:35:44,100
 And I wanna say, one day, I cannot wait to stand in heaven.

745
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:47,140
 And I don't know what it's gonna be like exactly,

746
00:35:47,140 --> 00:35:52,140
 but I'm gonna be looking around for Ken and Lois Thornton.

747
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:55,580
 Grandpa Ken, Grandma Lois, the Thorntons,

748
00:35:55,580 --> 00:35:56,900
 that New Zealand couple.

749
00:35:56,900 --> 00:36:00,420
 And I wanna shake their hand.

750
00:36:00,420 --> 00:36:01,460
 I'm gonna thank them.

751
00:36:01,460 --> 00:36:02,940
 Thank you.

752
00:36:02,940 --> 00:36:05,900
 Thank you for saying yes to my dad.

753
00:36:05,900 --> 00:36:09,580
 Thank you for opening your hearts and your home to my dad.

754
00:36:09,580 --> 00:36:11,460
 Thank you that you took him in,

755
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:15,020
 in his moment of crisis, in his darkest hour,

756
00:36:15,020 --> 00:36:16,700
 and you were there for him.

757
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:20,820
 And because of that, today, my dad is in heaven today.

758
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:23,260
 And that day, we will all be there.

759
00:36:23,260 --> 00:36:25,140
 I'm standing before you today,

760
00:36:25,140 --> 00:36:30,980
 because they said yes to God's heart for the fatherless.

761
00:36:31,300 --> 00:36:34,340
 And I just love that it's not just one man's life

762
00:36:34,340 --> 00:36:36,820
 that was transformed, right?

763
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:40,220
 God, in his grace and his glory,

764
00:36:40,220 --> 00:36:42,820
 he took what would have been a generational curse

765
00:36:42,820 --> 00:36:45,540
 and turned it into a generational blessing.

766
00:36:45,540 --> 00:36:47,980
 Not just one man's destiny redeemed,

767
00:36:47,980 --> 00:36:50,500
 but a whole clan, a whole tribe,

768
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:53,260
 all of our destinies redeemed.

769
00:36:53,260 --> 00:36:56,580
 And so again, can we just give God

770
00:36:56,580 --> 00:36:58,500
 a big, big hand for that?

771
00:36:58,500 --> 00:36:59,500
 It's all him.

772
00:37:00,620 --> 00:37:02,460
 It's God's story.

773
00:37:02,460 --> 00:37:06,700
 It's God's story, but we get to be a part of his story.

774
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,780
 So you might be saying, "Jason, okay,

775
00:37:08,780 --> 00:37:10,300
 "I wanna be a part of this story.

776
00:37:10,300 --> 00:37:12,620
 "This is touching, this is moving.

777
00:37:12,620 --> 00:37:14,500
 "I wanna help."

778
00:37:14,500 --> 00:37:17,260
 But to be honest, and we wanna be honest

779
00:37:17,260 --> 00:37:18,380
 'cause we are a family,

780
00:37:18,380 --> 00:37:20,380
 and we need to be honest with one another, right?

781
00:37:20,380 --> 00:37:22,300
 We have to be authentic.

782
00:37:22,300 --> 00:37:26,780
 Jason, this seems a bit too big and overwhelming.

783
00:37:26,780 --> 00:37:30,140
 I don't know, what if I'm not ready to adopt or to foster?

784
00:37:30,140 --> 00:37:32,180
 This just seems like a huge, huge step.

785
00:37:32,180 --> 00:37:33,940
 And you're right.

786
00:37:33,940 --> 00:37:35,900
 Adoption and fostering,

787
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:39,660
 these things may not be your portion right now or ever.

788
00:37:39,660 --> 00:37:42,180
 I don't know, that's between you and God.

789
00:37:42,180 --> 00:37:46,260
 But what I do know is that our God

790
00:37:46,260 --> 00:37:48,500
 has invited every single one of us

791
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:49,980
 to have a part to play.

792
00:37:49,980 --> 00:37:53,380
 Every one of us can do something, okay?

793
00:37:53,380 --> 00:37:56,660
 None of us should be trying to do everything.

794
00:37:56,660 --> 00:37:58,300
 None of us can do everything.

795
00:37:59,220 --> 00:38:02,500
 But all of us can do something.

796
00:38:02,500 --> 00:38:05,660
 And this is why I wanna end with this quote

797
00:38:05,660 --> 00:38:06,900
 from Mother Teresa.

798
00:38:06,900 --> 00:38:10,020
 It's a beautiful quote, right?

799
00:38:10,020 --> 00:38:12,220
 "Not all of us can do great things,

800
00:38:12,220 --> 00:38:18,340
 "but all of us can do small things with great love."

801
00:38:18,340 --> 00:38:25,100
 Wow, that challenges me so much,

802
00:38:25,100 --> 00:38:27,220
 but it also gives me great hope.

803
00:38:27,220 --> 00:38:28,260
 It gets me excited

804
00:38:28,260 --> 00:38:30,060
 because that means that I can do something,

805
00:38:30,060 --> 00:38:32,940
 we can do something.

806
00:38:32,940 --> 00:38:35,100
 And to help you get started,

807
00:38:35,100 --> 00:38:39,180
 here are a few next steps,

808
00:38:39,180 --> 00:38:41,420
 a little something for you, right?

809
00:38:41,420 --> 00:38:42,540
 'Cause we all need to ask the Lord,

810
00:38:42,540 --> 00:38:44,500
 what is that little something?

811
00:38:44,500 --> 00:38:47,100
 Okay, so it might be starting to pray

812
00:38:47,100 --> 00:38:52,780
 because this is a huge work.

813
00:38:52,780 --> 00:38:54,580
 There is a huge need.

814
00:38:54,580 --> 00:38:58,020
 There's a lot of spiritual warfare involved, okay?

815
00:38:58,020 --> 00:39:00,700
 And so prayer is the work.

816
00:39:00,700 --> 00:39:03,140
 It doesn't complete the work, it is the work.

817
00:39:03,140 --> 00:39:07,260
 And we love to say that it is not just hard work, right?

818
00:39:07,260 --> 00:39:09,340
 The work of caring for orphans and widows,

819
00:39:09,340 --> 00:39:11,620
 but it's also heart work.

820
00:39:11,620 --> 00:39:15,540
 And so the prayer, constant prayer in His presence,

821
00:39:15,540 --> 00:39:16,380
 crying out to Him,

822
00:39:16,380 --> 00:39:18,420
 that is something that we need to not just do the work,

823
00:39:18,420 --> 00:39:20,940
 complete the work, but also to sustain the work.

824
00:39:20,940 --> 00:39:23,180
 So please begin to pray.

825
00:39:23,180 --> 00:39:26,660
 Secondly is to support.

826
00:39:26,660 --> 00:39:28,100
 You know what, all around us,

827
00:39:28,100 --> 00:39:29,780
 where we live, work, and play,

828
00:39:29,780 --> 00:39:31,220
 where our kids go to school,

829
00:39:31,220 --> 00:39:32,620
 or where you go to school,

830
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:34,660
 there are adoptive families,

831
00:39:34,660 --> 00:39:35,860
 there are foster families,

832
00:39:35,860 --> 00:39:38,020
 there are families in crisis, right?

833
00:39:38,020 --> 00:39:40,300
 And there's many ways for all of us,

834
00:39:40,300 --> 00:39:42,380
 whether you're married or not married,

835
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:44,820
 whether you're working or retired, to get involved.

836
00:39:44,820 --> 00:39:47,300
 So for example, even in my own community,

837
00:39:47,300 --> 00:39:50,340
 you saw earlier the picture of our little village,

838
00:39:50,340 --> 00:39:52,260
 a bunch of the singles who are there,

839
00:39:52,260 --> 00:39:54,140
 they help with our kids' homework,

840
00:39:54,140 --> 00:39:56,460
 they help take them to play basketball,

841
00:39:56,460 --> 00:39:58,020
 they help them to,

842
00:39:58,020 --> 00:39:59,860
 tonight they're taking two of the older boys

843
00:39:59,860 --> 00:40:01,540
 to watch the Predator movie.

844
00:40:01,540 --> 00:40:02,620
 I don't know if that's a,

845
00:40:02,620 --> 00:40:04,580
 (laughs)

846
00:40:04,580 --> 00:40:05,420
 yeah, is it okay?

847
00:40:05,420 --> 00:40:06,340
 Okay, all right, yeah, yeah, yeah.

848
00:40:06,340 --> 00:40:08,180
 Okay, so, you know,

849
00:40:08,180 --> 00:40:10,980
 so there's a, everyone's contributing

850
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:11,980
 in their own little way.

851
00:40:11,980 --> 00:40:14,060
 Everyone's bringing out their five loaves and two fish,

852
00:40:14,060 --> 00:40:16,140
 and somehow there's more than enough.

853
00:40:16,140 --> 00:40:18,220
 Somehow, that's God's economy, all right?

854
00:40:18,220 --> 00:40:20,300
 So there's definitely ways

855
00:40:20,300 --> 00:40:23,260
 that you can begin supporting practically, okay?

856
00:40:23,260 --> 00:40:24,580
 And then the third thing, right?

857
00:40:24,580 --> 00:40:29,220
 Isaiah 117, learn to do good, right?

858
00:40:29,220 --> 00:40:33,060
 So we have set up on Thursday, December 4th,

859
00:40:33,060 --> 00:40:36,300
 in the evening here at the Vine Church here in Wan Chai,

860
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:39,540
 a info session just for you guys, all right?

861
00:40:39,540 --> 00:40:40,940
 So please do come,

862
00:40:40,940 --> 00:40:43,780
 and there'll be Mother's Choice professionals,

863
00:40:43,780 --> 00:40:46,420
 experts there, our social workers,

864
00:40:46,420 --> 00:40:49,700
 who will explain to you some different programs

865
00:40:49,700 --> 00:40:51,100
 and services and different ways

866
00:40:51,100 --> 00:40:54,540
 that you can start getting involved practically, okay?

867
00:40:54,940 --> 00:40:56,860
 But the bottom line is this.

868
00:40:56,860 --> 00:41:02,820
 We worship and serve a God who sees and loves the vulnerable.

869
00:41:02,820 --> 00:41:09,260
 And He's not afraid to draw near to us in our brokenness.

870
00:41:09,260 --> 00:41:12,020
 He loves us, He protects us,

871
00:41:12,020 --> 00:41:17,020
 and then He invites us and welcomes us into His family.

872
00:41:17,020 --> 00:41:23,620
 And then He invites us to do the same.

873
00:41:24,500 --> 00:41:29,500
 Can I close in prayer, and may I ask that we all stand?

874
00:41:29,500 --> 00:41:49,180
 Heavenly Father, thank You that You are our good,

875
00:41:51,820 --> 00:41:53,420
 good Father.

876
00:41:53,420 --> 00:41:59,300
 Thank You for all the mercy and the grace,

877
00:41:59,300 --> 00:42:04,300
 the unconditional love that You have showered upon us.

878
00:42:04,300 --> 00:42:09,820
 It's a steadfast and loyal love.

879
00:42:09,820 --> 00:42:13,580
 Your mercies never end towards us.

880
00:42:13,580 --> 00:42:17,060
 But You're not just our Father.

881
00:42:17,060 --> 00:42:19,420
 You're also the Father to the fatherless.

882
00:42:19,420 --> 00:42:20,660
 You're a defender of widows,

883
00:42:20,660 --> 00:42:23,020
 and You put the lonely in families.

884
00:42:23,020 --> 00:42:25,220
 This is also who You are.

885
00:42:25,220 --> 00:42:31,820
 And so God, today, would You come by Your Spirit

886
00:42:31,820 --> 00:42:35,140
 and do a new work in every single one of us,

887
00:42:35,140 --> 00:42:38,060
 that we would become more like You?

888
00:42:38,060 --> 00:42:42,740
 Can I invite You to lay hands on your own eyes?

889
00:42:42,740 --> 00:42:47,020
 God, would You open our eyes,

890
00:42:47,020 --> 00:42:50,340
 give us Your eyes to see the vulnerable?

891
00:42:50,860 --> 00:42:53,260
 To see those that society has forgotten,

892
00:42:53,260 --> 00:42:55,300
 the invisible, the marginalized.

893
00:42:55,300 --> 00:42:59,820
 Lord, help us to see them, God, to know them, Lord,

894
00:42:59,820 --> 00:43:02,820
 and to see their pain and their trauma.

895
00:43:02,820 --> 00:43:05,940
 Lord, may they never be invisible to us again.

896
00:43:05,940 --> 00:43:10,700
 And I invite You to put Your hands on Your heart.

897
00:43:10,700 --> 00:43:16,980
 God, would You awaken our hearts this afternoon?

898
00:43:18,540 --> 00:43:20,660
 Lord, forgive us for the times

899
00:43:20,660 --> 00:43:24,860
 that our hearts have been too hard or too numb, God,

900
00:43:24,860 --> 00:43:26,780
 or too small.

901
00:43:26,780 --> 00:43:28,940
 Lord, we repent for that.

902
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:33,380
 Holy Spirit, would You breathe upon our hearts now?

903
00:43:33,380 --> 00:43:34,860
 Would You stretch our hearts?

904
00:43:34,860 --> 00:43:36,220
 Would You soften our hearts?

905
00:43:36,220 --> 00:43:39,460
 Would You give our hearts, God, something new, Lord God?

906
00:43:39,460 --> 00:43:40,980
 Do something new in our hearts, Lord God,

907
00:43:40,980 --> 00:43:42,460
 that our hearts of stone

908
00:43:42,460 --> 00:43:44,820
 would be turned into hearts of flesh, Lord God.

909
00:43:44,820 --> 00:43:46,380
 This is a work of Your Spirit.

910
00:43:46,380 --> 00:43:47,780
 It requires a miracle.

911
00:43:47,780 --> 00:43:51,260
 It's a sign and a wonder, Lord, but we say yes, God.

912
00:43:51,260 --> 00:43:57,060
 We believe, God, that You can do this again, Lord, in us,

913
00:43:57,060 --> 00:44:01,340
 that we may feel what You feel

914
00:44:01,340 --> 00:44:04,940
 and care about what You care about

915
00:44:04,940 --> 00:44:07,580
 and love the way You love.

916
00:44:07,580 --> 00:44:11,940
 And lastly, can I invite You

917
00:44:11,940 --> 00:44:14,500
 to just hold hands with the people next to You?

918
00:44:14,500 --> 00:44:16,700
 Just grab the hand of the person next to You.

919
00:44:17,420 --> 00:44:22,420
 God, in Jesus' name right now, by Your Spirit,

920
00:44:22,420 --> 00:44:27,660
 would You just fall upon this congregation,

921
00:44:27,660 --> 00:44:30,060
 this community, the Vine Church.

922
00:44:30,060 --> 00:44:33,820
 Lord, would You commission Your family, the family of God,

923
00:44:33,820 --> 00:44:38,820
 would You empower them to rise up as a family of God

924
00:44:38,820 --> 00:44:43,820
 for this city, God, that they would father the fatherless,

925
00:44:43,820 --> 00:44:45,860
 they would defend the widows,

926
00:44:45,860 --> 00:44:48,460
 they would put the lonely in families, God,

927
00:44:48,460 --> 00:44:52,180
 so that many broken stories would be redeemed

928
00:44:52,180 --> 00:44:54,740
 and become beautiful testimonies?

929
00:44:54,740 --> 00:44:58,900
 God, all of this is for Your glory,

930
00:44:58,900 --> 00:45:02,860
 and all of this is for the sake of this city,

931
00:45:02,860 --> 00:45:05,740
 our city, and the next generation.

932
00:45:05,740 --> 00:45:08,180
 Lord, here we are.

933
00:45:08,180 --> 00:45:11,580
 May it be unto us as You say.

934
00:45:11,580 --> 00:45:15,260
 Send us, Lord.

935
00:45:16,260 --> 00:45:21,260
 We say yes once again, God, to You and to Your heart.

936
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:24,460
 In Jesus' name we pray, amen.

937
00:45:24,460 --> 00:45:25,300
 - Amen.

938
00:45:25,300 --> 00:45:28,740
 (congregation applauding)

939
00:45:28,740 --> 00:45:32,060
 (congregation cheering)

940
00:45:32,060 --> 00:45:35,560
 (congregation applauding)

941
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:45,560
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

